My meme

I just thought of this silly idea while thinking about trying 3d printing.

@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Sono&display=swap');
body {
  font-family: 'Sono', sans-serif;
}

p {
  font-style: italic; color: #0DEF28;

library(magick)

#create meme's objects
memetext <- image_read("memetext.png") %>% image_scale(200)

mememan <- image_read("stonkmeme.jfif") %>% image_scale(200)

meme_vector <- c(memetext, mememan)

meme <- image_append(meme_vector, stack = TRUE)
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My meme

This is my animated gif, i just found that these images look funny so I wanted to do something with them

library(magick)

#read and name frames
frame1 <- image_read('dogehungry.jpg') %>%image_scale(900)
frame2 <- image_read('dogeangry.jpg')%>%image_scale(400)
frame3 <- image_read('dogelook.jpg')%>%image_scale(400)
frame4 <- image_read('dogebonk.jpg')%>%image_scale(400)

#animate
gifmeme <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)
animation <- image_animate(gifmeme, fps = 0.5)
image_write(animation, "doge.gif")
